    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-02-12T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-02-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="1074"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1074">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 EW/2–1245</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Peruvian Embassy</gloss> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Department of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <p rend="center">
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Memorandum</hi>
                </p>
                <p>In compliance with the request made in the Memorandum of the Department of State,
                    dated February 12th, 1945,<note n="20" xml:id="d1074fn20">Not printed.</note>
                    the Peruvian Embassy considers that the terms “state of effective belligerency”
                    are equivalent to the expression “at war” as contained in the Declaration by the
                    United Nations.</p>
                <closer>
                    <dateline rendition="#left">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-02-12">February 12,
                            1945</date>.</dateline>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
